S3 Versioning

Keeps multiple versions of the same object in S3 bucket to keep track of the historical changes


Why versioning is important

Without Versioning

• File overwritten -> old data lost

• Accidental delete -> gone forever


With Versioning

• Restore previous versions

• Recover deleted files

• Track changes


What is a Delete Marker?

A delete marker is a special “placeholder” created when you delete an object in a version-enabled bucket.

Deleting an object in versioning enabled bucket will not actually remove the object.


Q: Can we delete an object permanently in the versioning enabled S3 bucket?

Yes, by deleting all the object versions


